OL,3,CTravellers face Easter bank holiday
OL,4,Cchaos after major train disruption
OL,6,FIn a statement, a Transport for Wales
OL,7,Fspokesperson said: "Due to signalling
OL,8,Fand power issues between Bridgend and
OL,9,FLlanelli, Transport for Wales was
OL,10,Funable to run services between Cardiff
OL,11,Fand Carmarthen and on the Heart of
OL,12,FWales line between Swansea and
OL,13,FShrewsbury.
OL,15,F"Services on the Maesteg line and Vale
OL,16,Fof Glamorgan line were also affected."
OL,17,FThey added: "We have been working
OL,18,Fclosely with Network Rail to resolve
OL,19,Fthis issue and are pleased to update
OL,20,Fthat the power issues have now been
OL,21,Fresolved.
